defaultand
default non-trans
defaultport solutions to accessibility problems. 
default
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultIdeally, public transport should provide a general service that is available, affordable, accessible and acceptable to all. Where this is not the case, certain groups are particularly vulnerable to experiencing is
defaultolation. PTEs are involved in a range of initiatives to ensure their needs are taken into account.
default
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultKey challenges associated with providing better and more consistent bus and rail services to isolated communities include funding; the deregulated nature of 
defaultthe bus market outside London; land-use planning decisions; and a lack of recognition among other sectors of the importance of transport to the successful delivery of their policy objectives.
default
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThe extent to which transport authorities can address these chal
defaultlenges is constrained by cuts to local government and transport funding, however, interventions include: the provision of tendered 'socially necessary' 
defaultbus 
defaultservices; use of alternative transport solutions; use of Local Transport Act 2008 powers; more effic
defaultient use of existing transport resources; and marketing and behaviour change initiatives. 
default
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultC
defaultonnecting isolated communities to services and opportunities is the responsibility of all those involved in the planning and delivery of public services - not just 
defaultthe transport sector.
default
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultCommunity Transport is effective at understanding the needs of local people but, as services come under increasing pressure, operators 
defaultface challenges in ‘scaling up’
default to meet demand or make the most of opportunities for sustainability
default. Capacity building as well as closer working with transport authorities could be helpful.
default
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultServices in isolated communities should be tailored to demand. If demand levels suggest that a taxi or demand-responsive transport would meet the needs of communitie
defaults, then provision of these services should be sufficient. However, it is important to ensure that these services are
default well publicised as well as
default affordable, accessible and acceptable to users.
