defaultoluntary 
defaultPartnership Agreements
default with bu
defaults operators to improve services
default. All PTEs ar
defaulte investing heavily in voluntary partnerships to benefit passengers.
default
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultMade it easier for transport authorities to facilitate voluntary Qualifying Agreements (QA) between competing operators to coordinate their timetables. 
default
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultExpanded the scope of Statutory Qu
defaultality Partnerships
default (SQPs)
default whereby binding agreements can be voluntarily entered into between 
defaulttransport authorities
default and bus operators, including on
default fares, frequencies and timings
default. PTEs were the first to introduce an SQP (in Sheffield) and a number of other 
defaultagreements have b
defaulteen reached since, with Bath and North East Somerset Council being the first to make a scheme embracing the full range of measures available.
default
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultMade Quality Contracts (QC
defaults
default) a more realistic option. A QC involves replacing the existing deregu
defaultlated bus markets with a franchising system (similar to that in London) where the local transport authority specifies what the bus network will provide and the private sector competes for the right to provide it. Services to 
defaultisolated communities can be spe
defaultcified as an integral part of the package that 
defaultoperators
default bid for
default, allowing cross-subsidisation of such services by more profitable routes
default. 
defaultSeveral PTEs are developing proposals for QCs, with Nexus the first to launch a formal public consultation.
